ng starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def checkValid(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> bool:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom itertools import chain\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def checkValid(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> bool:\n        n = len(matrix)\n        return all(len(set(row)) == n for row in chain(matrix, zip(*matrix)))\n```\n\nThis solution uses the `chain` function from the `itertools` module to iterate over both the rows and the columns of the matrix. For each row and column, it converts the row or column into a set and checks if the length of the set is equal to `n` (the size of the matrix). If all rows and columns satisfy this condition, the matrix is valid, and the function returns `True`. Otherwise, it returns `False`.", "estimated_date": 1641686400000}